{
  "texts": [
    "Consensus-building models come in a wide variety.",
    "This is due to the fact that each blockchain has a distinct type of data entry and a varied projected threat level.",
    "Based on the anticipated level of threat, the blockchain chooses the consensus algorithm it will employ.",
    "For instance, because they anticipate a very high level of threat, Bitcoin and Ethereum adopt a powerful consensus method called proof-of-work (PoW).",
    "Moreover, a simpler and quicker consensus method is used by blockchains designed to store financial transactions between well-known parties.To decide how to validate existing transactions and add new transactions to the blockchain, a consensus mechanism is also utilized."
  ]
}